  "description": "Axel Efraim Blixt was a Swedish editor born on October 25th, 1900 in S. Hestra, Jönköping County. He was the son of Anders Johan B. and Emma Blixt. He studied lantmäteri (land surveying) from 1918-1919 and folkhögskola (adult education) in 1922. Blixt had a long career in journalism and worked for various newspapers, including Smålands Landsbygd in Vimmerby, Smålandsbygdens Tidning in Jönköping, Sörmlandsbygden, Norra Hallands Veckoblad in Kungsbacka, and Hallands Nyheter in Varberg. Blixt was married to Wivi Johansson in 1935 and they had three children: Lennart, Christina, and Anders."
